The paper deals with compressed sensing measurements and signal detection, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of sparse vectors and the optimization of the detection criteria suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the proposed detector to spectrum sensing involves numerical analysis and optimization, which could place the paper in the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
